      <title>[Letter] 1815 Jul. 18, New York [to] John Dickenson, Nashville, Tennessee / Samuel Ferguson</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter written by Samuel Ferguson to John Dickenson on July 18, 1815. In the letter, Ferguson asks Dickenson to collect a debt from a George Poyzer and give the proceeds to a man named William Seger. Ferguson also includes directions as to how the debt of $1298.00 is to be collected and paid.</abstract>
